# guest-utils — Scripts that run INSIDE VMs
#
# These scripts are meant to be copied to guest VMs and run there.
# They live on the host at /opt/proxmox-utils-hetzner/guest-utils/
#
# Copy to VM:
#   scp /opt/proxmox-utils-hetzner/guest-utils/<script> root@10.10.10.X:/opt/
#
# Or copy all:
#   scp /opt/proxmox-utils-hetzner/guest-utils/*.sh root@10.10.10.X:/opt/
#
# Scripts:
#   (none yet — vm-guest-publish.sh is auto-generated by vm-publish.sh)
#
# Future ideas:
#   - docker-setup.sh      — install Docker + compose, configure logging/rotation
#   - backup-volumes.sh    — snapshot Docker volumes to host via rsync
#   - ssl-setup.sh         — Caddy/Traefik + Let's Encrypt auto-config
#   - monitoring.sh        — node-exporter / promtail / basic health checks
#   - update-system.sh     — apt upgrade + docker image pulls + cleanup
